</p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
Personal life</st>

<p>

He was married three times, the second to biologist <scientist wordnetid="110560637" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../639/4656639.xml">
Anne McLaren</link></scientist>
 from 1952 to 1959.  He had four children, one by his first wife, and three by Prof. McLaren, including economist <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<economist wordnetid="110043643" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<social_scientist wordnetid="110619642" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<academician wordnetid="109759069" confidence="0.8">
<scientist wordnetid="110560637" confidence="0.8">
<adult wordnetid="109605289" confidence="0.8">
<professional wordnetid="110480253" confidence="0.8">
<educator wordnetid="110045713" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../326/5832326.xml">
Jonathan Michie</link></educator>
</professional>
</adult>
</scientist>
</academician>
</causal_agent>
</social_scientist>
</person>
</economist>
</physical_entity>
 and health psychologist <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../827/8786827.xml">
Susan Fiona Dorinthea Michie</link>.  Michie and McLaren remained friends after their divorce, and became close again after the death of his third wife.</p>
<p>

Michie aged 83 and his ex-wife McLaren died in a car crash on July 7, 2007 whilst they were travelling from Cambridge to London.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref></p>

